Chief Complaint: pt states f/u with complaints of chest discomfort and SOB.
History of Present Illness
Copy Gregory Dabov, M.D.; Garretson Ellis, M.D.; L. Madison Michael, M.D.; Carole Simon, M.D.; Daniel Lynn Thompson, M.D.; Keith Williams, M.D.
I had the pleasure of seeing Sylvia Green in our office today for followup evaluation. As you know, she is a 70-year-old female with the above listed cardiac diagnoses. She was last seen in the office on 2020-12-01. In the interim, she had her right knee replaced 2021-04-15 and left knee replaced 2021-07-17. She states that in 2021-04-17 her potassium was elevated and she was given Lokelma. She complains of chest pain that lasts 10-15 minutes and only occurs with activity for the past 3 days when she gets up to go to the bathroom. She has shortness of breath with this, but no nausea or diaphoresis. It has been occurring daily, but states she has been feeling better overall for 2 weeks. She has dyspnea on exertion at 50 feet. She is on oxygen at 3-4 liters in the past 2 weeks. She is getting physical therapy 3 times per week. She complains of lower extremity swelling, 2-pillow orthopnea, and racing, fluttering, skipping palpitations lasting 30 seconds. She denies PND. She states her energy has been worse the past 2 days.
Heart rate 71, blood pressure 140/80.
EKG: Sinus rhythm with negative T waves, possible anterior ischemia.
IMPRESSION AND PLAN:
Ms. Green has the above listed cardiac diagnoses. I will check a CBC, chem-12, lipid profile, magnesium, BNP and act accordingly based on result. I have asked her to increase her torsemide to 20 mg 2 tablets p.o. b.i.d. We will consider increasing her potassium chloride after review of her labs. We have scheduled her for a left heart catheterization and echocardiogram for 2021-12-30. I have asked her to continue all her current medications and to see us again in 1 month.
The patient was discussed and evaluated with Dr. Edwards.
Dictated by Stacy Ellis, FNP.
